2 Customize on this report

This section explains how to quickly customize this report by changing the value of some parameters. You can find or add the parameters in the meta-tab of your xlsx-file (ext/report/kmev2021/james-kmev2021.xlsx) in the column which has type = report. For example, if you dont want the current section in your report, you can disable it by setting parameter report_include_james_appendix = n.

A tip to quickly test text without repeatedly recreating your figures is setting create = n in your globals-tab. If you dont specify the create parameter in your meta-tab, no report and no figures will be created. So, setting create = y only for your report (in the meta-tab), makes sure, only the report itself is generated (i.e. without the figures). This makes it possible to change/update the text and watch the resulting report quicly. In the end, i.e. before creating the final report, you can put the original settings back and then generate the full report.

2.1 Choose output format (html, pdf)

Please use report_format to indicate which report output formats you want. The default is html. You can choose from:

  1. document options
  • html
  • pdf
  • word [under development; this may not work]
  1. presentation options
  • ioslides [under development; this may not work]
  • slidy [under development; this may not work]
  • powerpoint [under development; this may not work]
  • beamer [under development; this may not work]

You can choose one or more options at the same time (e.g. report_format = html, pdf).

2.2 Edit the front page

In the report column of your xlsx-file, you can set the parameters title, author and date to customize the title, author and date that are shown at the start of this report. For example, author = prof.dr.ir. Great Me will update the author as given here.

2.3 Customize the text in this report

This section explains the simplest way to create your own custom report from Excel. First create a new tab in ext/report/kmev2021/james-kmev2021.xlsx for your custom text. Lets assume the name of this new tab is my-custom-report. Now add tab = my-custom-report to the meta-tab in your xlsx, in the column which has type = report.

The text in this column will now appear in your report instead of the default text and figures.

2.3.1 Reproduce the out-of-the-box report

Before doing anything fancy, lets first explain how to reproduce the report as it is now. Open the tab youve just created and add the content of this code snippet. Please try whether this indeed gives you the exact same report. You can now add text and extend your report.

2.3.2 Adding custom text to your report

The text you type in the Excel-tab may be accross multiple lines. You can put each line in a new cell. However, please use the first column only.

2.4 Troubleshooting

In case of odd behaviour, you can manually inspect the generated Rmd- and md-files of this report in /Users/mdijkstra/Dropbox/cpb/git/james/./generated/report. The subdirectory generated of this directory contains the separate figures in this report. Please beware, dont edit the generated Rmd- or md-files as they are overwritten each time again.
